Inputs\: keyName - the context key for the number you want to increment increment - the value to increment, defaults to 1 Responses\: success - completed task 5b262995-7371-4223-8fac-31333a4406d6.5c6bf9ea-863b-422e-ba0a-68af6f96e6f7.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

5b262995-7371-4223-8fac-31333a4406d6.620eae7f-24ab-41a4-8922-de89c1618168.description=
Scans for a specified HTML flag and returns everything between that flag and its closing flag. For example\:
if flag is table then then everything between  and 
 is returned. The function does support nested tables, specifically if the html had\:

foo


bar




moo


The inner table (bar) will NOT be gotten. But foo or moo can be, and if foo is gotten it will contain the sub-table bar.

inputs\:
occurrenceNumber - which flagged section to return, 1 \= first section, 2 \= second. 0 will return the entire document.
flag - the html flag to parse on, in the above example this was table
html - the html to parse.
type - The type of the html flag. If the  then set this to "unclosed" In this case only the htmlParamNames and htmlParamValues results should be used.

returns - The information between  and 

Extra Results\:
htmlParamNames - The names of all parameters in the  header.
htmlParamValues - The names of all values that correspond to htmlParamNames.

Responses\:
success - the specified flag was returned.
failure - The parse failed, the html does not have enough occurrences of flag.

5b262995-7371-4223-8fac-31333a4406d6.description=
Takes an html document, and parses the current value of a form's inputs.
NOTE\: if the form is nested inside another form, you should pass in the parent form, and the index (starting at 1) of the subform you want.

inputs\:
html - the html to be parsed. This can be read from a webpage using the http client get operation.
form number - Which form should be parsed, starting at 1 for the first form.
namesKey - A context key name in which to store The names of the input name/value pairs.
valuesKey - A context key in which to store the values of the input name/value pairs.

Responses\:
success - The form was parsed successfully.
failure - Parsing failed.

Extra Results\:
namesKey and valuesKey will have the name/value pairs from the form put into them. These name/value pairs are the same that are required to post (though any values that are being updated will need to be changed).
